# secretscanignore for ragappv3
# Prevents vocabulary false positives on security review scans.
# Each line is a glob pattern matched against scanned file paths.
# Patterns may carry a trailing `# defensive: <reason>` comment to silence the
# stale-glob advisory emitted by scripts/check_secretscan.py — use it for
# patterns that legitimately match nothing today but guard paths that may
# appear in other checkouts or future states.
# Test fixture files are not real secrets.
backend/tests/**
# Documentation directories that contain "password" / "token" /
# "secret" in prose, never as real credentials.
docs/**
# Configuration examples are not real credentials.
config.example.json  # defensive: optional example, may not exist in every checkout
.env.example
# Build and dependency files reference package names that trigger
# vocabulary matches but contain no actual secrets.
package-lock.json
bun.lockb  # defensive: bun lockfile is not used by this repo but is a known vocab-trigger filename
**/*.lock
**/*.lockb
**/requirements*.txt
**/Pipfile*  # defensive: Pipfile is not used by this repo but is a known vocab-trigger filename
# Markdown documentation may include review notes that look like
# secrets to a vocabulary matcher but are documentation only.
**/*.md
**/CHANGELOG*
# Type stubs and protocol files are part of the runtime; the "secrets"
# in their names are part of typed interfaces, not values.
backend/app/services/__init__.py  # defensive: file may not exist in all refactors; interface-name trigger
backend/app/__init__.py
backend/app/api/__init__.py  # defensive: file may not exist in all refactors; interface-name trigger
backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py  # defensive: file may not exist in all refactors; interface-name trigger
# Generated documentation (skills, plans, post-mortems) may contain
# review notes that look like secrets; they never contain real values.
**/post-mortem*
**/run-receipts/**  # defensive: opencode-swarm runtime receipts dir; absent in ragappv3 but pattern kept for plugin parity
**/plan-export/**  # defensive: opencode-swarm plan-export dir; absent in ragappv3 but pattern kept for plugin parity
**/skill-improver/**  # defensive: opencode-swarm skill-improver dir; absent in ragappv3 but pattern kept for plugin parity
# The PR review skill in the swarm plugin directory is not source code
# shipped with the application.
**/skills/swarm-pr-review/**  # defensive: skill body documents PR-review findings templates that look secret-like but are docs
**/.opencode/**
**/.agents/**
**/.claude/**
